From: Magnus Karlsson <magnus.karlsson@intel.com>
Date: Mon, 10 May 2021 11:38:53 +0200
Subject: ixgbevf: add correct exception tracing for XDP
Patch-mainline: v5.13-rc5
Git-commit: faae81420d162551b6ef2d804aafc00f4cd68e0e
References: bsc#1113994 FATE#326315 FATE#326317

Add missing exception tracing to XDP when a number of different
errors can occur. The support was only partial. Several errors
where not logged which would confuse the user quite a lot not
knowing where and why the packets disappeared.

Fixes: 21092e9ce8b1 ("ixgbevf: Add support for XDP_TX action")
Reported-by: Jesper Dangaard Brouer <brouer@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Magnus Karlsson <magnus.karlsson@intel.com>
Tested-by: Vishakha Jambekar <vishakha.jambekar@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tony Nguyen <anthony.l.nguyen@intel.com>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbevf/ixgbevf_main.c |    3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbevf/ixgbevf_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbevf/ixgbevf_main.c
@@ -1101,11 +1101,14 @@ static struct sk_buff *ixgbevf_run_xdp(s
 	case XDP_TX:
 		xdp_ring = adapter->xdp_ring[rx_ring->queue_index];
 		result = ixgbevf_xmit_xdp_ring(xdp_ring, xdp);
+		if (result == IXGBEVF_XDP_CONSUMED)
+			goto out_failure;
 		break;
 	default:
 		bpf_warn_invalid_xdp_action(act);
 		/* fallthrough */
 	case XDP_ABORTED:
+out_failure:
 		trace_xdp_exception(rx_ring->netdev, xdp_prog, act);
 		/* fallthrough -- handle aborts by dropping packet */
 	case XDP_DROP:
